\par
Our notes on Continuous Wave Laser Operation have produced a lot of designs, and this is possibly the most difficult one to bring into reality: a deuterium-fluoride laser weapon the size of an ordinary pistol.\par
\par
The difficulty in making this a reality will be to get the parts small enough and light enough so that they will:\par
\par
1) Fit into a pistol-sized package, and\par
2) Be light enough to aim and fire one-handed.\par
\par
